1
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:14,800
<i> Our child is dead.</i>

2
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:16,133
<i> Dad's here.</i>

3
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,167
<i> I'm too late.</i>

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,733
<i>We went through hell
after you left us.</i>

5
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:22,100
<i>I was forced to marry a man
I didn't love,</i>

6
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:23,500
<i>just so Jessica would have
a father.</i>

7
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,567
<i> It was a huge mistake.</i>

8
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:27,200
<i> Because Manuel was cruel.</i>

9
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:32,000
<i>My children and their father
are my inspiration.</i>

10
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:38,500
<i>So I could spend Christmas
with my family.</i>

11
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:44,567
<i>While I'll never get to spend
Christmas with my child.</i>

12
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:45,867
<i> He's got some nerve.</i>

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,800
<i>He's lucky I still see him
as a patient.</i>

14
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:53,600
<i>Honestly, I could've crippled
him for good.</i>

15
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:04,133
Sir! Sir!

16
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:06,000
- Are you okay, Sir?
- I'm so sorry, Sir.

17
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,167
Oh, it's okay. I'm fine.

18
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,900
Sorry about that, Sir.
I just lost my balance.

19
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,767
- Sorry again.
- It's fine.

20
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,633
Thank you for saving me.

21
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,967
- Are you okay, Sir?
- I'm fine.

22
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:19,567
Let me help you.
Let's take a break, Sir.

23
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,633
All right.

24
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:22,967
Thanks.

25
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,467
Jojo...

26
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:30,533
thank you so, so much.

27
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:34,300
I lost my balance.

28
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,733
I thought I was going to fall.

29
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:38,567
Good thing
Jojo's like The Flash.

30
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,167
He caught me just in time.

31
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:44,567
How can we ever thank you?

32
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:52,500
Just tell me what you need.

33
00:01:52,633 --> 00:01:54,333
Oh no, Ma'am, it's nothing.

34
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,567
Sir Manuel's safety
is my responsibility.

35
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,767
I made sure
that he didn't get hurt.

36
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:06,067
You're even proud
to report that to me?

37
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,500
Your therapist friend
attempted to hurt Manuel.

38
00:02:09,967 --> 00:02:12,367
What if he rats you out?
What an idiot.

39
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:19,167
He won't talk.

40
00:02:19,433 --> 00:02:20,267
I paid him.

41
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:22,367
Careful. Take it slow.

42
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:31,533
What were you thinking?

43
00:02:31,933 --> 00:02:33,233
Why did you do that?

44
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,767
We just wanted to scare Manuel
a little.

45
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:40,200
You should've seen
his face earlier.

46
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:41,833
In the end,

47
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,767
I even looked like the hero
to his family.

48
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,100
What if something went wrong?

49
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:48,867
What if you went too far?

50
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,133
What if Manuel actually died?

51
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:55,567
Why are you reacting like that?

52
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,233
So what if he got hurt?

53
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:01,700
I've been holding a grudge
against that family anyway.

54
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,433
And I already want revenge.

55
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:05,300
Why?

56
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:07,267
Do you still love him?

57
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,833
Is that why you're so concerned?

58
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:10,367
What are you talking about?

59
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,967
All I'm saying is,

60
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,167
you should've hurt
the children first.

61
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:16,367
We lost a child.

62
00:03:16,967 --> 00:03:18,900
They should be the ones
you're taking revenge on.

63
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,967
Jeff, where are you?

64
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,933
We want to eat
ice cream already.

65
00:03:31,067 --> 00:03:33,000
My favorite flavor, okay?

66
00:03:33,133 --> 00:03:34,600
Take care. Bye!

67
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:39,767
Ma'am, good thing you're home.

68
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:42,067
Do you know
how much I missed you?

69
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,033
It really feels different

70
00:03:43,167 --> 00:03:45,300
when the light of the household
is here.

71
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:46,733
Of course, Didang.

72
00:03:46,867 --> 00:03:50,567
No matter how many
Christmas lights we put up,

73
00:03:51,067 --> 00:03:53,833
nothing compares to the light
mom brings.

74
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Of course.

75
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:57,833
Aunt Felma isn't the
"light of the home" for nothing.

76
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:00,833
You just said the same thing.

77
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:02,800
What matters is that...

78
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,600
we're all together
this Christmas,

79
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:07,600
and everyone's safe.

80
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:14,067
Thank you all so much.

81
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:18,633
I'm so happy.

82
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:22,267
I'm finally home.

83
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:27,267
And I'm with the people I love.

84
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,700
So let's make sure

85
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:33,033
we never forget this Christmas.

86
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:40,067
It's so important for a child

87
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,833
to celebrate Christmas

88
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,467
with their family.

89
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,100
For years, I dreamed of...

90
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:55,433
spending Christmas
with you and our child.

91
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:59,200
I wish I could've spent
just one Christmas...

92
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,833
with Jessica.

93
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,200
But that will never
happen now...

94
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:12,367
because they killed our child.

95
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,900
So they don't deserve
to celebrate Christmas

96
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:19,100
until we get our revenge.

97
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:22,600
Which of their children do
you want me to start with?

98
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:25,067
Coleen.

99
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:28,900
She's the one with the most
hatred and jealousy to Jessica.

100
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,000
It's only right
that she pays first.

101
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:42,300
You know, this is my first
Christmas with dad.

102
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:44,167
And there's even a bonus guest.

103
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,400
- Who?
- Joel!

104
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:52,767
Well then, you and Joel are
teaming up in the kitchen, okay?

105
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:58,933
Because Jeffrey and I are
only good up to the prep part.

106
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,700
Aren't you the one in charge
of the barbecue?

107
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,833
Oh, wait. We've got it, right?

108
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,300
- It might get burned.
- No, she can handle it.

109
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:11,067
Hey!

110
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,067
The war's starting!

111
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:15,200
Oh, is that so?

112
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,400
- Oh, boy.
- You're really cute, Joel.

113
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:19,000
- You're really cute!
- Hey!

114
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:20,300
No, I like it well-done!

115
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,733
- I really like it burnt.
- I'm getting annoyed.

116
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:24,133
Hey, I've been annoyed at you
for a long time now.

117
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:26,900
- These are two! Two!
- Sis! Sis! This is oil!

118
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:29,367
No, you know,
I mean, it's not like...

119
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,167
I don't actually have any
real anger toward you, guys.

120
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:31,967
You scared me!

121
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,767
Honestly, I'm mad with this one!

122
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,867
- Hey!
- Go on! Go on!

123
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,900
Come on!

124
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:40,800
What's that?

125
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:41,767
Stop it!

126
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:42,833
- Fight me!
- That's enough!

127
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:44,000
Fight me!

128
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,300
- Wait!
- Fight me right now!

129
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:46,833
Wait, wait, wait!

130
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:49,933
I told you, Jojo, don't schedule
work on Christmas.

131
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:52,333
Oh, Sir, we don't
really have holidays.

132
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:53,567
And besides, Sir,

133
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:55,100
it would be a waste to stop
Ma'am Felma's PT sessions

134
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:57,167
with all her progress.

135
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:00,867
All right, come on in first.

136
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,167
Oh, thank you, Sir.

137
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:06,133
Hey, hey, hey.

138
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:08,500
That's enough,
we've got a guest!

139
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:11,067
You guys, seriously.

140
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,167
Oh, we have a guest.

141
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,833
Hi, Ma'am Felma.

142
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,933
Jojo, Merry Christmas!

143
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:17,200
Merry Christmas.

144
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,667
Oh, thank you so much,
by the way.

145
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:22,100
Mom and dad have improved
so much because of you.

146
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,500
Oh, it's nothing.

147
00:07:26,067 --> 00:07:27,833
Come on in. Let's have snacks.

148
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:30,200
- Let's go.
- Yeah, come on.

149
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,967
- Come on.
- It's not even cooked yet.

150
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,300
What's that?

151
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:34,767
- Go ahead, Mom.
- Sir, I feel shy.

152
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:37,100
No, don't be shy.
Go on. Come on.

153
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:39,300
It's just us anyway.

154
00:07:39,433 --> 00:07:40,200
Come in.

155
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,733
Didang.

156
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:45,233
- Hi.
- Sit here, Mom.

157
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:46,567
Thank you.

158
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:52,500
Jessica?

159
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:57,400
Do you know our youngest sister?

160
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,833
<i> As Jessica grew up,</i>

161
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:12,567
<i>I realized my decision
was completely wrong.</i>

162
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:16,767
<i> Because Manuel was cruel.</i>

163
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:22,000
<i>Then I found out he already had
another family before us.</i>

164
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:24,133
Sir Manuel mentioned her to me.

165
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:27,267
It's a shame
you never got to meet her.

166
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:29,933
She was very kind.

167
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:32,867
Are you okay?

168
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,467
I'm sorry.

169
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:39,333
I just suddenly missed Jessica.

170
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:44,800
Oh, before you start crying,
come on.

171
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:48,300
We're having snacks.
We prepared so much.

172
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:49,533
Didang?

173
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:50,633
Sit down.

174
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,367
- You're not like that with us.
- Let me. Let me.

175
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,667
Come on, sit here.
We prepared a lot.

176
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,467
There's salad. Everything.
Come on.

177
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,067
I'll set everything up, okay?

178
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,333
Come on.

179
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:00,367
You're not even done mixing,
and you're already serving?

180
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,400
Come on, hurry it up.

181
00:09:04,667 --> 00:09:06,933
Go ahead, Ma'am.
Careful with your steps.

182
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:09,333
There, slowly.

183
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:12,333
If anything hurts, we stop.
Okay, Ma'am?

184
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:13,633
All right.

185
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:15,167
Slowly, Ma'am.

186
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,900
- Okay.
- I can...

187
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,233
walk a bit now.

188
00:09:20,367 --> 00:09:22,067
Wait a second, Ma'am.

189
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,900
Even without the walker.

190
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:26,467
Ma'am, you can't do that yet.

191
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:29,233
My balance is fine now.

192
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:32,000
Not yet, Ma'am.
You still need it.

193
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:37,100
We're trying to avoid
you falling.

194
00:09:37,233 --> 00:09:41,300
That's why it's important
you keep using it.

195
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,967
It really feels nice seeing you
celebrate Christmas.

196
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,533
With a complete family.

197
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,800
Only now.

198
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:01,500
There were many...

199
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:06,633
Christmases we spent...

200
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:09,400
without Manuel.

201
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,700
Me...

202
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:21,933
I never really got to celebrate
Christmas because...

203
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:25,200
my child died.

204
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:30,100
Manuel told me about it.

205
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,067
You lost a child.

206
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:35,967
Yes.

207
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:38,067
What hurts most...

208
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,967
is that I wasn't with her
when she died.

209
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:43,567
Her mother and I were separated.

210
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,733
Sorry.

211
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,200
Sorry.

212
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:04,633
I feel sad for you.

213
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,633
<i> You have no right to feel sad.</i>

214
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:10,667
<i> Guilt.</i>

215
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,200
<i>That's what you're supposed
to feel.</i>

216
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,500
<i> Because you killed my child.</i>

217
00:11:20,567 --> 00:11:21,867
You're really lucky.

218
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:24,033
Your family is complete.

219
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:27,133
You're with your children.

220
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:30,600
They're my greatest treasure.

221
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:35,133
When I had a tumor...

222
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:39,300
I was afraid...

223
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,900
of dying...

224
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:50,400
because I didn't want
to leave them unprepared.

225
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,700
So I fought.

226
00:11:56,167 --> 00:12:02,600
And I keep fighting for them.

227
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:09,267
Wait.

228
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,633
Just a moment, Ma'am. Hold on.

229
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,633
Easy now, Ma'am.
Let's sit down here first.

230
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,833
I told you we shouldn't
force it. Hold on.

231
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:21,833
There.
Where does it hurt, Ma'am?

232
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:24,200
Here? Okay.

233
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,367
I'm going to lift it slowly,
all right?

234
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,267
There.

235
00:12:30,133 --> 00:12:33,267
- It hurts.
- Ma'am...

236
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:37,600
I'm sorry, Ma'am,
but this is part of the therapy.

237
00:12:37,733 --> 00:12:39,300
I need to press a bit

238
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:45,100
so you'll feel better
and walk properly again.

239
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:47,067
It'll hurt a little.

240
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:51,633
<i> Yes, Felma.</i>

241
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:53,133
<i> Endure it.</i>

242
00:12:53,267 --> 00:12:54,533
<i> Don't complain</i>

243
00:12:54,667 --> 00:13:00,133
<i>because there's a lot more pain
coming for you and your family.</i>

244
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,367
There, Sis.

245
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,933
We're almost done
wrapping the gifts.

246
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:09,467
There.

247
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,833
Which one's mine? Let me see!

248
00:13:12,967 --> 00:13:14,800
You startled me!

249
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:17,933
You really have
no emotional intelligence.

250
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,367
- You can't even wait.
- Emotional intelligence?

251
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:23,633
Don't worry,
our gift for you is nice.

252
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,533
- She's right.
- And it's expensive.

253
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:27,667
Ten thousand pesos.

254
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:32,400
You know, there's only one thing
that can make me happy.

255
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,100
My wife and child.

256
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,700
Calling me,

257
00:13:38,167 --> 00:13:39,400
and just hearing their voices
would be enough,

258
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,867
especially Tetay's.

259
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:49,100
Andrea, I'll give my gift to
Jeffrey to lessen his sadness.

260
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:52,067
There. That one.

261
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:54,400
There.

262
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:58,700
- What's that? It's big.
- Advance Merry Christmas.

263
00:13:58,833 --> 00:13:59,600
Wow, it's heavy.

264
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:01,333
What is this?

265
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:02,433
I'll open it now, okay?

266
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:03,633
I'm opening it.

267
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,433
I knew you were going
to get sentimental.

268
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:14,633
I just didn't expect it
this early.

269
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:18,100
So there, you can get drunk
early and rest.

270
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,433
- Merry Christmas.
- Very nice.

271
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:23,133
You can start getting
sentimental early.

272
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:25,467
Thanks, Bro. That's great.

273
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,400
Sir, be careful.

274
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:30,700
Slow steps.

275
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:35,500
If you feel any stiffness
or pain, we stop. Okay, Sir?

276
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:37,367
- Okay.
- Slowly.

277
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:40,300
So, where are you
spending Christmas Eve?

278
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:42,700
Oh, just at the dorm, Sir.

279
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:46,567
If you like, you can stay here
and celebrate with us.

280
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,400
Oh no, Sir.
That would be too much.

281
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:51,233
And I'm used to not
celebrating anyway.

282
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:52,833
Well, up to you...

283
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:55,667
but if you change your mind,
just come back.

284
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,633
You're always welcome here.

285
00:14:58,833 --> 00:14:59,800
Thank you, Sir.

286
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,867
Sir, your children...

287
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:05,833
are very kind.

288
00:15:05,967 --> 00:15:08,367
Even though Jessica
wasn't their real sibling,

289
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,500
they treated her like one.

290
00:15:11,933 --> 00:15:13,167
Especially Coleen.

291
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:17,100
They never saw Jessica
as a half-sister.

292
00:15:17,933 --> 00:15:18,867
Because...

293
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:21,900
Felma accepted her.

294
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:24,800
She treated her
like her own child.

295
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:30,167
That's why Jeffrey,
Andrea, and Coleen

296
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,033
also accepted her
as a real sister.

297
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,867
<i>When they found out Jessica
wasn't really their sibling,</i>

298
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,367
<i> they hurt her.</i>

299
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,300
<i> They abused her.</i>

300
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:45,200
<i>They mistreated Jessica until
the child became depressed.</i>

301
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,367
<i> Until our daughter died.</i>

302
00:15:48,133 --> 00:15:53,167
Sir, are you and Jessica's
mother not on good terms?

303
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,300
Let's not talk about that.

304
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:01,367
I don't want to remember what
happened between us back then.

305
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,067
<i> You've got some nerve, Manuel.</i>

306
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:07,900
<i>After you used Hazel
and drained her dry,</i>

307
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:10,200
<i>now you're avoiding
talking about her?</i>

308
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:16,267
- Looks like we're done.
- Oh, Sir.

309
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:18,300
- Time went by fast, didn't it?
- Yes, Sir, it really did.

310
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:19,800
Sir, I'll be heading out now.

311
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:22,933
I still have to stop
by Southcrest.

312
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:27,633
Oh, perfect.
That's on our way, too.

313
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:29,767
If you like,
you can ride with us.

314
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:32,233
The only thing is, we'll
be stopping somewhere for a bit,

315
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:33,767
if that's okay with you.

316
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:34,467
Oh, sure.

317
00:16:35,033 --> 00:16:35,733
Thank you.

318
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:48,667
Sir.

319
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,900
Thank you.

320
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:56,500
Sir, so this is where
you're going?

321
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:58,733
Yes, it won't take long.

322
00:16:58,867 --> 00:17:00,700
I just want to greet my child.

323
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,567
Jo, want to come with me?

324
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:08,667
- Sir?
- Yeah, so you can meet Jessica.

325
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:09,733
Come on.

326
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:26,767
Dear.

327
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:41,500
Dad, I'll just wait in the car,
okay?

328
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:42,533
All right, Son.

329
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,733
Bye, Jessica!

330
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:54,467
I come here early
so I don't run into my wife...

331
00:17:56,567 --> 00:17:59,967
I mean, Jessica's mother.

332
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:04,400
Oh, yeah.
She's not your child...

333
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:05,767
with Miss Felma.

334
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:09,167
Losing a child is hard,
isn't it, Sir?

335
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:12,400
Very.

336
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:17,633
It's like losing a part
of your body.

337
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,567
She was far too young to die.

338
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:28,433
I didn't even get the chance to
repay all the love she gave me.

339
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:32,600
I still had so many plans
for her.

340
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:34,967
For us.

341
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:40,367
You know,
I loved my youngest so much.

342
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:46,033
She was the reason
I kept fighting in life.

343
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:58,233
It feels unfair.

344
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:01,200
God took her back too soon.

345
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:05,667
But I know there was a reason.

346
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:08,300
And it's not for me
to question anymore.

347
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,367
What matters is that...

348
00:19:14,533 --> 00:19:16,367
she got justice.

349
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:21,133
Merry Christmas, Jessica.

350
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:26,267
I love you so much, my child.

351
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:29,967
Let's go, Jojo.

352
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,500
Thanks for coming with me.

353
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:41,167
<i>What happened to you
will only have justice</i>

354
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,133
<i>when these animals finally pay.</i>

355
00:19:45,033 --> 00:19:46,667
<i> The ones who abused you</i>

356
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,833
<i> and hurt you, Jessica.</i>

357
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:53,367
<i>Your death won't be meaningless,
my child.</i>

358
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:57,067
<i> I'll avenge you.</i>

359
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,733
I'm confused, Hazel.

360
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,433
I hate Manuel,

361
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:17,167
Felma,

362
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,167
and their children so much.

363
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:22,733
But they seem fine.

364
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,900
It feels like they
accepted Jessica.

365
00:20:26,667 --> 00:20:30,900
They even have a family photo
displayed with my child in it.

366
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,967
That family is good
at pretending.

367
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,867
So don't let yourself be fooled,

368
00:20:36,467 --> 00:20:37,967
especially by Felma.

369
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:41,200
That woman has a sweet tongue.

370
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,033
And Manuel...

371
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,067
is a great actor.

372
00:20:45,667 --> 00:20:47,933
They pretend they loved Jessica.

373
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:52,200
But the only ones he really love
are Felma's children.

374
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,733
Jeffrey, Andrea, and Coleen.

375
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:57,167
When it came to Jessica,
she meant nothing to him.

376
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,267
But from what I saw,

377
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,567
Manuel seemed to have
really loved Jessica.

378
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:16,400
The way he talks about her, it's
like my child was truly his.

379
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:20,500
Manuel's just a good actor.

380
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:22,567
If he admits

381
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:24,500
that I fooled him into believing
Jessica was his,

382
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:25,900
that would be humiliating
for him.

383
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:27,800
Of course, he'd keep up the act.

384
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:33,967
But the truth is that he never
really loved our child.

385
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:37,467
He just doesn't want
the truth to come out.

386
00:21:38,233 --> 00:21:41,467
That they mistreated our child

387
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,467
when they found out she was
my child with another man.

388
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:52,500
Jo...

389
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:57,733
Manuel only ever loved
his first family.

390
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:00,267
From then until now.

391
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:06,267
But Manuel never loved me,
especially Jessica.

392
00:22:07,267 --> 00:22:08,967
He just used us

393
00:22:09,967 --> 00:22:11,867
to give his family
a better life.

394
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,500
But the truth is,

395
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:17,300
they're bad people.

396
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:23,967
You know...

397
00:22:26,967 --> 00:22:28,300
maybe it would be better

398
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:30,367
if you didn't go through
with your plan

399
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,533
to take revenge for Jessica.

400
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:35,767
I mean...

401
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:37,967
what's the point?

402
00:22:38,533 --> 00:22:40,033
She's gone, right?

403
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:42,233
Our child is gone.

404
00:22:43,033 --> 00:22:44,167
She's dead.

405
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:52,667
No.

406
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,000
I've already started this.

407
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,433
I'm going to finish it.

408
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:04,900
Where did you go?

409
00:23:05,033 --> 00:23:06,867
Hey!

410
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:11,833
I can't stand seeing
that monstrous family happy.

411
00:23:11,967 --> 00:23:13,733
Who will you go after first?

412
00:23:13,867 --> 00:23:15,400
Mom? Dad?

413
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:16,967
I feel like someone's
following me.

414
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:18,833
Run, sweetheart!

415
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,033
Andrea.

416
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,000
You can go ahead to the car.

417
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,333
I just need to use
the restroom first.
